                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13978323" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 23 Apr 2014 15:46:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1589442&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1589442&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13979456" author="tmueller" created="Thu, 24 Apr 2014 08:40:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With the test case (but without applying the rest of the patch), I can not consistently reproduce the issue, even if I change from MicroKernelException to IllegalStateException, and even if I use more threads and a longer loop. But setting a breakpoint at the exception works. I will try to change the test case to better report the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13979501" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 24 Apr 2014 09:21:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The failure is hidden because throwing the MicroKernelException there results in a retry of the merge in AbstractNodeStoreBranch. If you change it to IllegalStateException &lt;b&gt;and&lt;/b&gt; apply the changes to AbstractNodeStoreBranch, you should see the test fail pretty consistently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13979544" author="tmueller" created="Thu, 24 Apr 2014 10:14:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have tested the patch, it looks good to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think in the future, we will need even more tests to verify all possible code paths and combinations are covered. For example, the first change in NodeDocument.isConflicting is not tested (the &quot;delete&quot; case), but I don&apos;t currently see how it could be efficiently tested. We would need very special timing conditions. Maybe with a custom DocumentStore that pauses in a programmable way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13979545" author="tmueller" created="Thu, 24 Apr 2014 10:14:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 to apply the patch in the 1.0 branch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13979547" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 24 Apr 2014 10:20:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged into 1.0 branch in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1589658&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1589658&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14017557" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Wed, 4 Jun 2014 10:16:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;bulk close for the 1.0 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
